Weather experts discussed the drought

Thursday and its possible causes and effects, and said they hoped to produce a consensus on how much longer it will last.
"There's an enormous number of possibilities that one could chase.
The next business of the scientist is to eliminate the possibilities of ... and extend the range of analysis and look for cause and effect," said David Rodenhuis, director of the federal Climate Analysis Center in Washington.
The symposium attended by 13 state and national experts was sponsored by The Weather Channel, an Atlanta-based cable network, which broadcast the meeting live.
